# L-SON Implementation Standards

L-SON is a token-efficient format used when users pass the `--format lson` flag.

## Formatting Rules
- Use the `@` prefix for all keys.
- Use uppercase for keys (e.g., `@ID`, `@STATUS`, `@TITLE`).
- Do not use JSON braces, brackets, or quotes unless they are part of the value content.
- Example structure:
  ```text
  @ID: CORE-101
  @STATUS: DOING
  @PRIORITY: CRITICAL
  @TITLE: Task Title Here
  @DESC: Markdown description...
  ```
  